Pop the @rice noodles{150%g} into a #mixing bowl{}. Pour on enough boiling water to submerge them. Leave to soak for ~{10-12%minutes}.

> The noodles will soften and cook in this time.

When cooked, drain the noodles in a #colander{}, cool under running water and return to the bowl.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Sprinkle the @Thai style spice mix{1/2%tsp} over both sides of the @British chicken breasts{2} (use less if you don't like spice). Add the chicken to the pan and brown for ~{1-2%minutes} on each side.

Lower the heat to medium, add the @water{50%ml} and cover with a tight fitting #lid{}. Cook for ~{10%minutes}.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1}, then remove the core from the pepper and thinly slice. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @echalion shallot{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all). Zest, then juice the @lime{2}. Crush or finely chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}.

Heat a splash of oil in another frying pan over high heat. When hot, stir-fry the pepper and shallot until softened, ~{3%minutes}. Transfer to a #bowl{}, we will add them to the noodles later.

Mix the lime zest, @mirin{15%ml}, @soy sauce{25%ml} and lime juice together in a small bowl. Stir in the @sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} and half the coriander.

Shred the chicken using two #forks{}. Toss the noodles, veggies and dressing together in the bowl. Serve, topped with the chicken. Finish with a sprinkling of the peanuts and coriander. Enjoy!